The paper is primarily focused on network security and detecting P2P botnets, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of network flow analysis and community behavior analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The clustering of bots into communities and the use of machine learning techniques for detection may also suggest relevance to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
